Tom Emerson wrote:

> ...
>
> Yowza, lots. Here's an excerpt or two representative issues.
>
> 12/19/2004 10:47:18 +0000 SEVERE org.archive.crawler.fetcher.FetchHTTP 
> innerProcess CrawlURI(http://www.hicourt.gov.cn/law/newlaw.asp?da=3) 
> <http://www.hicourt.gov.cn/law/newlaw.asp?da=3%29> RIS still open. 
> Should have been closed by method release: ToeThread #13
>
This is a check on our way out of FetchHTTP.  The RecordingInputStream 
should be closed
at this point in the processing.

> 12/19/2004 10:47:18 +0000 WARNING 
> org.archive.crawler.extractor.ExtractorHTML innerProcess Failed get of 
> replay char sequence 
> CrawlURI(http://www.hicourt.gov.cn/law/newlaw.asp?da=3) 
> <http://www.hicourt.gov.cn/law/newlaw.asp?da=3%29> Illegal response 
> body offset of 179 whereas size is only 0 ToeThread #13
>
This logging is a symptom of the above observation.

> 12/19/2004 10:50:16 +0000 WARNING 
> org.archive.crawler.frontier.KeyedQueue dequeue NoSuchElement 
> Exception dequeuing from queue ADMIN01

Does the URL http://www.hicourt.gov.cn/law/newlaw.asp?da=3 trigger a 
midfetch abort?

The closing of the RIS is supposed to be done down in the guts of 
httpclient.  Its releaseConnection may not be completing by the time we 
go to use the RIS.

St.Ack



<http://www.hicourt.gov.cn/law/newlaw.asp?da=3%29>
